HEADWORD: Inspissation
<hw>In`spis*sa"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act or the
process of inspissating, or thickening a fluid substance, as by
evaporation; also, the state of being so thickened.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>inst.</ent>⟦br⟧
